					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The problem could be with your RAM adapter. The BIOS doesn't use all of the Character RAM. Maybe there is a problem with an address line on the chip. It could be that a solder joint went bad or the chip somehow is damaged or not working now. I would try another RAM adapter if that is a reasonable option for you.</div>

