					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">So, here's the thing that makes this Really Weird:<br /><br />In SMB (LL), sometimes the right lower half of his body is made of a reflection of the left lower half. Same exact tile. Coming from the exact same place in memory. Which is what seems to on screen in both the original photo you posted and at least the latter of the two you have here. And yet, Mario's right half is distorted, and his left half isn't.<br /><br />In Moero TwinBee, I haven't even the foggiest idea where that &quot;half bubble&quot; image is coming from: I don't see it in the pattern tables. It's supposed to be a simple 5x5 sprite (padded into an 8x16 cell, hence &quot;half&quot; bubble). <br /><br />Buh. I have really no idea what could be causing this ... it's definitely not simply the adapter's CHR RAM, if that's even to blame at all. I don't suppose you might have access to another famicom to test on, also ?</div>

