						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">lidnariq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">In SMB (LL), sometimes the right lower half of his body is made of a reflection of the left lower half. Same exact tile. Coming from the exact same place in memory.</div><br />SMB and SMB2 (J) do this to save 3 tiles on the sprite side of the pattern table, 1 for small Mario and 2 for Super Mario, even though it twists Mario's legs into a painful <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turnout_%28ballet%29" class="postlink">turnout</a>. This was fixed in Doki Doki Panic and SMB3, and the versions of SMB and SMB2 (J) in Super Mario All-Stars use the SMB3 graphics for Mario.</div>

